1 POSTDOCTORAL AND 1 PH.D. POSITIONS AT LIUPPA=20

(UNIVERSITY PAU &AMP; PAYS ADOUR)=20

SUMMARY=20

We are looking for two HIGHLY-MOTIVATED RESEARCHERS (1 POSTDOC AND 1 PH.D. =
STUDENT) to propose a new GENERIC BUSINESS INFORMATION SYSTEM THAT IS CUSTO=
MIZABLE WITH RICH MULTIMEDIA SERVICES CONCERNING DATA INDEXATION, STORAGE, =
ENRICHMENT, SECURITY AND PRESENTATION for several domains, and especially E=
nergy and Environment applications. In the LIUPPA lab, the selected candida=
te will develop research activities related to DATA MODELING AND REASONING,=
 INFORMATION RETRIEVAL, SEMANTIC WEB (e.g., Linked Data and ontologies), AN=
D PRIVACY PROTECTION.=20

CONTEXT AND OBJECTIVES=20

The ever-increasing need for extracting, managing, storing, publishing and =
retrieving data from heterogeneous contents has become a major concern in m=
odern large-scale projects. This is particularly observed in many applicati=
on domains where several actors (with different expertise, roles, preferenc=
es and rights) exchange a great amount of information at any stage of a pro=
ject. As an example, in the construction industry, actors (i.e., owners, co=
nsultants and contractors) exchange contracts, technical specifications, ad=
ministrative forms, technical drawings and on-site photos throughout the di=
fferent stages of a construction process. The interchanged documents, origi=
nated from different sources, do not usually have a common standard structu=
re. Also, they show heterogeneity in their formats (e.g., pdf, docx, xlsx, =
jpeg, etc.), contents (e.g., architecture, electrical, mechanical, structur=
e, etc.), media types (e.g., image, text, etc.) and versions.=20

Consequently, there is a crucial need to help any project actors: (1) TO IN=
TEGRATE, TO STORE, TO MODEL AND TO INDEX LARGE COLLECTIONS OF DATA, especia=
lly multimedia data; (2) TO ACCESS DATA according to specific needs and pre=
ferences with a user-friendly system; and (3) TO OFFER ADDED-VALUE SERVICES=
, such as data enrichments and/or data security. We would like to PROPOSE A=
 PERSONALIZED BUSINESS INFORMATION SYSTEM FOR VARIOUS COMPANIES OR ORGANIZA=
TIONS.=20

Offering such a generic and tunable system to any companies or organization=
s raises many research challenges that we have listed and detailed hereafte=
r.=20

1. DATA INTEGRATION, MODELING, STORING AND INDEXING:=20

o MULTIMEDIA CLOUD: the system should consider any types of contents (multi=
media documents, sensors data=E2=80=A6) and any specific metadata models. T=
his information would be incorporated and stored in a Cloud-based infrastru=
cture. Hence, users would have access to such a data at anytime, anywhere a=
nd anyhow. The cloud would also be used to execute (on-demand or not) speci=
fic indexing processing/services to complete the metadata.=20

o DATA REPRESENTATION AND OPTIMIZED INDICES: In recent research publication=
s (Charbel et al., INFORSID 2017 [1] and DEXA 2017 [2]), we have proposed a=
n ontology based-model that combines existing metadata standards (e.g., DC,=
 TEI, EXIF, MPEG-7) and introduces new components augmenting the capabiliti=
es of these standards. This model offers a pluggable layer that makes it ad=
aptable to different domain-specific knowledge. To validate our model, we h=
ave conducted experiments with Nobatek (www.nobatek.com), a French technolo=
gical resource center which is involved in the sustainable construction dom=
ain. More precisely, its main role is to ensure the compliance of a constru=
ction project with the environmental standards and quality performance.=20

The RDF and OWL W3C standards have been used to implement our model, howeve=
r the instances based on these languages may be verbose in syntax and may c=
ontain redundancies, hence slowing down query treatments and inferences (Re=
gina et al., ER 2015 [3]). Consequently, as done in the Information Retriev=
al research domain, optimized indices would be defined in the project.=20

2. DATA ACCESS:=20

o USER NEEDS AND PREFERENCES: the system should consider various kind of us=
ers with different expertise levels and roles. Consequently, the system has=
 to handle various vocabularies used by different communities and to align =
these terms if needed for adapting the results presentation.=20

o QUERY REPRESENTATION AND OPTIMIZED PROCESSING: Many standard query langua=
ges (e.g., SQL and SPARQL) can be used to retrieve information. However, us=
ers that are not experts in databases or semantic web technologies cannot s=
pecify such kind of technical queries. Hence, the system may guide the user=
 interactively to find his/her desired information. In this project, specif=
ic actions will be devoted to user-friendly query specification and query r=
ewriting.  =20

3. ADDED VALUE SERVICES:=20

o /ENRICHMENTS:/ the system should connect its internal resources to extern=
al data, such as Open Data and/or Linked Open Data. These connections could=
 contextualize data, i.e., present more details about a concept or some rel=
ated contents.=20

o /ANONYMIZATION AND SECURITY:/ the system may contain sensitive data and/o=
r data with specific rights (legacy aspects). The system should protect the=
se data or anonymize them automatically if needed.=20

o /MATCHING, RESULTS PRESENTATION AND NAVIGATION:/ the system should offer =
a user-friendly interface to end-users to present his/her results and let h=
im navigate through them by considering all the handled data and connection=
s. It may also consider data preferences and security.=20

CANDIDATE SPECIFICATION=20

We are looking for two excellent researchers (1 Postdoc and 1 Ph.D. student=
) in Computer Science. The candidates should have:=20

o Experience in Data Modeling, Information Retrieval and the Semantic Web (=
e.g., Linked Data and ontologies);=20

o Strong programming skills in Java and Web programming languages;=20

o Excellent writing and communication skills in English;=20

o A good ability to communicate with others; =20

o The ability to work autonomously.=20

Good Theoretical background would be a plus. Experience in Multimedia Cloud=
 and Big Data will be a plus too. And French language knowledge would be ap=
preciated.=20

HOW TO APPLY=20

The applicant will be required to send a detailed up-to-date CV, two refere=
nces (one of which must be academic), the last acquired diploma with grade =
results, one or two best publications and a covering letter by email to: Ri=
chard.Chbeir@univ-pau.fr, Sebastien.Laborie@univ-pau.fr and Christian.Salla=
berry@univ-pau.fr. In the email subject, indicate if the application is for=
 the Postdoc or the Ph.D. position.=20

THE DEADLINE TO APPLY IS 10TH DECEMBER 2018 but consideration of candidates=
 will continue until the position is filled.=20

START DATE AND SALARY=20

The start date is by EARLY 2019.=20

The postdoctoral and Ph.D. positions will be funded by a grant from the Uni=
versity of Pau, and especially E2S (Energy and Environment Solutions): Post=
doc gross salary of 2300 euros/month and Ph.D. student gross salary 1880 eu=
ros/month.=20

LOCATION AND ENVIRONMENT=20

o LOCATION: Univ. Pau & Pays Adour.=20

o ENVIRONMENT: The researchers will integrate the T2I group of LIUPPA lab (=
http://liuppa.univ-pau.fr). The project is conducted in partnership with in=
dustrials. =20

-------------------------

[1] Nathalie Charbel, Christian Sallaberry, S=C3=A9bastien Laborie, Gilbert=
 Tekli, Richard Chbeir: LinkedMDR: un mod=C3=A8le s=C3=A9mantique de repr=
=C3=A9sentation de corpus de documents multim=C3=A9dia. In /Actes du 35=C3=
=A8me congr=C3=A9s INFormatique des ORganisations et Syst=C3=A8mes d=E2=80=
=99Information et de D=C3=A9cision (INFORSID 2017)./ =20

[2] Nathalie Charbel, Christian Sallaberry, S=C3=A9bastien Laborie, Gilbert=
 Tekli, Richard Chbeir: LinkedMDR: A Collective Knowledge Representation of=
 a Heterogeneous Document Corpus. In /Proc. of the 28th International Confe=
rence on Database and Expert Systems Applications (DEXA 2017)/. Springer LN=
CS. =20

[3] Regina Ticona-Herrera, Joe Tekli, Richard Chbeir, S=C3=A9bastien Labori=
e, Irvin Dongo, Renato Guzman: Toward RDF Normalization. In /Proc. of the 3=
4th Int. Conf. on Conceptual Modeling (ER 2015)/, pp. 261-275, Springer LNC=
S.   
