            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style=3D"margin-left: 7=
5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; backg=
round-attachment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% =
0%; background-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Courier =
New&quot;;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">o</span> <strong><span style=
=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:la=
ng=3D"EN-US">User needs and preferences:</span></strong> <span style=3D"fon=
t-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"E=
N-US">the system should consider various kind of users with different exper=
tise levels and roles. Consequently, the system has to handle various vocab=
ularies used by different communities and to align these terms if needed fo=
r adapting the results presentation.</span>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style=3D"margin-left: 75p=
t; text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; backgro=
und-attachment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% 0%=
; background-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Courier =
New&quot;;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">o</span> <strong><span style=
=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:la=
ng=3D"EN-US">Query representation and optimized processing:</span></strong>=
 <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"E=
N-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">Many standard query languages (e.g., SQL and SPARQ=
L) can be used to retrieve information. However, users that are not experts=
 in databases or semantic web technologies cannot specify such kind of tech=
nical queries. Hence, the system may guide the user interactively to find h=
is/her desired information. In this project, specific actions will be devot=
ed to user-friendly query specification and query rewriting. &#160;</span>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style=3D"margin-left: 39=
pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; backgr=
ound-attachment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% 0=
%; background-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <strong><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial,=
 sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">3.</span></strong> <strong>=
<span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN=
-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">Added value services:</span></strong>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style=3D"margin-left: 7=
5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; backg=
round-attachment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% =
0%; background-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Courier =
New&quot;;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">o</span> <strong><em><span st=
yle=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml=
:lang=3D"EN-US">Enrichments:</span></em></strong> <span style=3D"font-size:=
 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">t=
he system should connect its internal resources to external data, such as O=
pen Data and/or Linked Open Data. These connections could contextualize dat=
a, i.e., present more details about a concept or some related contents.</sp=
an>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style=3D"margin-left: 75p=
t; text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; backgro=
und-attachment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% 0%=
; background-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Courier =
New&quot;;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">o</span> <strong><em><span st=
yle=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml=
:lang=3D"EN-US">Anonymization and security:</span></em></strong> <span styl=
e=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:l=
ang=3D"EN-US">the system may contain sensitive data and/or data with specif=
ic rights (legacy aspects). The system should protect these data or anonymi=
ze them automatically if needed.</span>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left: 75pt; text-=
align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: none; background-atta=
chment: scroll; background-color: white; background-position: 0% 0%; backgr=
ound-repeat: repeat repeat;">
                <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: &quot;Courier =
New&quot;;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">o</span> <strong><em><span st=
yle=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" lang=3D"EN-US" xml=
:lang=3D"EN-US">Matching, results presentation and navigation:</span></em><=
/strong> <span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;" l=
ang=3D"EN-US" xml:lang=3D"EN-US">the system should offer a user-friendly in=
terface to end-users to present his/her results and let him navigate throug=
h them by considering all the handled data and connections. It may also con=
sider data preferences and security.</span>
            </p>
            <p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin: 12pt 0cm 6pt 36pt; text=
